    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-05T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-05T05:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 793.94/518</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-05T18:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1916, 6 p.m</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>As a result of a collision between Chinese and Japanese troops at Chengchiatun,
                    Mongolia, in connection with military action against so-called Mongolian
                    revolutionists, instigated, equipped and directed by Japanese in a similar way
                    as in Shantung recently, the Japanese Government is now demanding of the Chinese
                    Government creation of Japanese police forces in places where Japanese sojourn
                    and the appointment of Japanese advisers to the China police; it is also
                    suggesting appointment of Japanese military advisers and instructors; all this
                    in addition to the usual indemnities and apologies.</p>
                <p>While these demands refer to Manchuria and Eastern Mongolia, yet, unless the
                    Chinese are able to safeguard themselves, dangerous precedent for all of China
                    would be established.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
